column5: This is wholesome. I love it.

same dude. Like family would care...sure. but the version they would be talking about, praising, crying over...isn't even me. They'll be mourning some other person and say all kinds of bullshit. They don't actually know me. Acting like I was such a lovely and wonderful person, some perfect child as they sob. Give me a fucking break.

There's only person who actually knows me and would get it right. But she means a lot to me, I don't want to hurt her with that. Plus she lives 6000+ miles away.
